â™ª And I wander around

16:42.369 --> 16:45.003
â™ª And I wander around

16:45.738 --> 16:49.674
â™ª It's here
then it's gone â™ª

16:50.609 --> 16:53.211
Look, I destroy
everything I touch.

16:53.213 --> 16:55.513
I don't wanna destroy you.

16:55.515 --> 16:58.549
Okay, well, if you haven't
already noticed,

16:58.551 --> 17:01.085
I'm not really
the easily destroyed type.

17:01.087 --> 17:03.421
â™ª Didn't even have time

17:03.423 --> 17:04.555
â™ª To get it straight...

17:04.557 --> 17:05.757
Let's go.
This is horrible.

17:05.759 --> 17:07.458
I don't want you ever
coming here again.

17:07.460 --> 17:10.128
No, see, I come here
all the time.

17:10.130 --> 17:11.629
That's the thing.

17:11.631 --> 17:14.365
Listen to me.

17:15.300 --> 17:18.770
This is not who you are.

17:18.772 --> 17:20.838
Okay?

17:20.840 --> 17:22.940
You are more
than the worst thing

17:22.942 --> 17:24.475
that has ever happened
to you.

17:24.477 --> 17:27.145
Oh, yeah?
Yeah.

17:27.147 --> 17:29.714
Yeah, you are.

17:31.183 --> 17:34.685
And I lied before.

17:34.687 --> 17:36.521
You did destroy me,

17:36.523 --> 17:40.091
but I've never
been happier.

17:43.929 --> 17:47.432
â™ª Watch the sun go down

17:47.434 --> 17:51.469
â™ª I watch the sun go down

17:58.177 --> 18:00.812
Who are you expecting?
Max.

18:00.814 --> 18:02.346
Max?
Yeah.

18:02.348 --> 18:03.481
(Gabe)
Hi, Grant.

18:03.483 --> 18:05.616
Oh, it's for you.

18:05.618 --> 18:08.519
Okay.
Good to see you, too.

18:08.521 --> 18:09.353
Hi.
Wow--

18:09.355 --> 18:10.521
Hey.
Yeah, we should just go.

18:10.523 --> 18:14.125
I-- I forgot
my sweater.

18:14.127 --> 18:16.194
Hey.
Hi.

18:16.196 --> 18:17.528
Hi.

18:17.530 --> 18:18.362
You look nice.

18:18.364 --> 18:21.599
Hey, man, that's my line.
Making me look bad.

18:21.601 --> 18:22.433
Grant.

18:22.435 --> 18:23.734
Oh, finally you're here.

18:23.736 --> 18:25.369
Let's go.
Okay.

18:28.173 --> 18:29.740
Have fun.

18:29.742 --> 18:32.076
Yeah, we intend to.

18:32.078 --> 18:36.114
You know, I'm really starting
to like that guy.

18:36.116 --> 18:37.949
Me, too.

18:39.685 --> 18:41.018
(knocking)

18:41.020 --> 18:42.286
Come in.

18:44.223 --> 18:45.089
Hey, sorry
to bother you.

18:45.091 --> 18:50.228
I just had the most unexpected
conversation with my mom.

18:50.230 --> 18:50.628
Oh?

18:50.630 --> 18:55.032
Apparently, she bought
a overnight spa getaway

18:55.034 --> 18:55.633
at a silent auction.

18:55.635 --> 18:58.236
She was planning on
bringing her friend Lois,

18:58.238 --> 19:01.539
but then Lois suddenly
needs a hip transplant.

19:01.541 --> 19:04.775
Is anyone in this story
under the age of 70?

19:04.777 --> 19:06.110
Yeah, I know.

19:06.112 --> 19:09.247
Well, she wants me
to go with her.

19:09.249 --> 19:12.083
The room has
a hot tub, uh, facials,

19:12.085 --> 19:15.586
and something called
a chromatic color wrap.

19:15.588 --> 19:18.356
And 24 hours
of nonstop criticism.

19:18.358 --> 19:21.826
After four decades,
I think I can handle it.

19:21.828 --> 19:23.127
It is Monday night.

19:23.129 --> 19:25.496
It's okay
if I go, right?

19:25.498 --> 19:26.197
Sure.

19:26.199 --> 19:29.033
You've been working so hard
you deserve a break.

19:29.035 --> 19:31.102
Well, I'd rather
go with you.

19:32.638 --> 19:34.071
Well...

19:34.073 --> 19:37.875
it wouldn't be
the same.

19:38.677 --> 19:42.113
I'll let you
get back to work.

20:03.235 --> 20:06.070
Oh... sorry.

20:06.072 --> 20:09.774
You seem
pretty happy.

20:09.776 --> 20:12.009
Yeah, I guess I am.

20:12.011 --> 20:15.846
I don't suppose I'm gonna get
any more information on that.

20:15.848 --> 20:16.881
Nope.

20:16.883 --> 20:19.750
Well, you know what,
as long as you're happy.

20:19.752 --> 20:23.721
If parents had a flag,
that would be our motto.

20:23.723 --> 20:25.122
We just want
our kids happy.

20:25.124 --> 20:27.091
Is there enough
in there for me?

20:27.093 --> 20:29.227
No.
Yeah.

20:29.229 --> 20:31.095
Have some.

20:31.097 --> 20:32.630
Here you go.

20:32.632 --> 20:34.131
Thanks.

20:34.133 --> 20:36.067
You know,
there's not enough, uh,

20:36.069 --> 20:38.035
junk food
in this house.

20:38.037 --> 20:38.736
We've got five people.

20:38.738 --> 20:41.505
We need more than just
one pint of ice cream.

20:41.507 --> 20:42.840
We've got
gluten-free cookies.

20:42.842 --> 20:44.909
Oh, no.
Have you tried those?

20:44.911 --> 20:46.143
Those things
are terrible.

20:46.145 --> 20:47.912
Wait, didn't you
buy them?

20:47.914 --> 20:48.246
Yes.

20:48.248 --> 20:51.148
I wanted a cookie that didn't
make me wanna eat cookies.

20:51.150 --> 20:54.118
But I don't think
that feeling ever goes away.

20:54.120 --> 20:56.554
Even babies, you know,
they can only drink milk.

20:56.556 --> 20:57.622
I think they're thinking,

20:57.624 --> 21:00.891
"You know what this milk
could really use?

21:00.893 --> 21:02.460
A cookie."

21:02.462 --> 21:04.061
Oh.

21:04.063 --> 21:05.563
I think you just
made a joke.

21:05.565 --> 21:08.466
I am not an animal,
I am a human being.

21:08.468 --> 21:13.771
I know it's-- it's like
Arnold Schwarzenegger gone bad.

21:13.773 --> 21:14.572
You're too young.

21:14.574 --> 21:15.673
You don't know
that reference.

21:15.675 --> 21:17.575
Yeah, I do.
It's "The Elephant Man."

21:17.577 --> 21:20.244
Yeah, my mom used--

21:22.180 --> 21:24.415
She used to be
really into movies.

21:24.417 --> 21:25.650
It was kind of
her thing.

21:25.652 --> 21:28.052
Every time
I'd get sick or anything,

21:28.054 --> 21:29.487
she'd, like,
sit with me in bed,

21:29.489 --> 21:31.322
and we'd watch movie
after movie.

21:31.324 --> 21:36.127
Kind of like a mini film-
festival, but with the flu.

21:36.129 --> 21:36.694
Anyway, sorry.

21:36.696 --> 21:39.096
I'm sure you don't wanna hear
about any of that.

21:39.098 --> 21:43.934
I was actually thinking
how grateful I am to her.

21:44.202 --> 21:48.973
She made you very happy,
gave you a great life.

21:53.211 --> 21:56.547
That's a really amazing thing
for you to say.

21:58.383 --> 22:00.351
Thank you.

22:05.057 --> 22:08.059
Well, you have the rest.

22:08.061 --> 22:10.628
I have
a court case Monday

22:10.630 --> 22:13.931
that I have to
prepare for.

22:13.933 --> 22:15.599
Good luck,
I hope you win.

22:15.601 --> 22:16.133
Thanks, me, too.

22:16.135 --> 22:18.502
I'll finally get
that Crash off the street.

22:18.504 --> 22:19.337
He's so worthless.

22:19.339 --> 22:21.472
Don't talk about him
like that.

22:21.474 --> 22:23.240
That's horrible.

22:23.242 --> 22:25.943
I thought you were
done with him.

22:25.945 --> 22:27.812
Well, I'm not.
Since when?

22:27.814 --> 22:29.013
Since today,
actually.

22:29.015 --> 22:31.949
Okay, well, at least
it's not serious.

22:31.951 --> 22:32.516
It is serious.

22:32.518 --> 22:34.719
You don't know
what kind of life he's led.

22:34.721 --> 22:36.187
I'm sure
it's been tough,

22:36.189 --> 22:38.689
and maybe it's to blame
for what he's become.
Maybe?

22:38.691 --> 22:43.561
But it doesn't matter anymore,
because now it's who he is.

22:43.563 --> 22:46.364
How can you
even say that?

22:47.999 --> 22:53.170
That boy has had no one
to believe in him...

22:53.172 --> 22:55.473
ever.

22:57.342 --> 22:58.242
Now he does.

22:58.244 --> 23:01.512
I don't think the judge that's
going to see him on Monday

23:01.514 --> 23:04.415
is gonna share
your optimism.

23:06.985 --> 23:07.852
Why?
What's gonna happen?

23:07.854 --> 23:11.222
This is his second arrest--
a fairly sizable bust--

23:11.224 --> 23:13.891
and from what I can tell,
his only defense

23:13.893 --> 23:15.126
is "I just won't
do it again ."

23:15.128 --> 23:18.062
No judge is going to buy that
with his juvie record.

23:18.064 --> 23:20.231
Carter,
he's going to prison.

23:20.233 --> 23:23.033
For-- For how long?

23:23.035 --> 23:25.603
At least three years.

23:27.172 --> 23:28.773
Is that definite.

23:28.775 --> 23:30.541
No, it--

23:30.543 --> 23:33.344
it could be five,
it could be ten.

23:33.346 --> 23:35.312
Carter...

23:35.314 --> 23:37.948
baby, believe me,
he knows this.

23:37.950 --> 23:39.483
And the fact
that he didn't tell you

23:39.485 --> 23:42.820
he's about to go to prison
is all the information

23:42.822 --> 23:45.689
you need to know
about this boy.

23:45.691 --> 23:46.390
Yes, it does.

23:46.392 --> 23:49.627
It tells me he's not
gonna be there on Monday.

23:56.768 --> 23:58.002
Today was perfect.

23:58.004 --> 24:00.037
Yeah.

24:00.039 --> 24:01.038
Yeah, I know.

24:01.040 --> 24:02.206
I would've been
the last perfect day

24:02.208 --> 24:03.407
you ever would've had
with me.

24:03.409 --> 24:07.411
I couldn't end today telling you
I was about to go to prison.

24:10.148 --> 24:12.450
Well...

24:12.452 --> 24:15.219
today isn't over yet.

24:15.221 --> 24:20.524
â™ª

24:23.495 --> 24:24.295
â™ª I'm coming for you

24:24.297 --> 24:26.397
â™ª You better
as fast as you can â™ª

24:26.399 --> 24:27.598
Oh, I suck at this.

24:27.600 --> 24:29.433
Listen, everyone
sucks at this.

24:29.435 --> 24:32.570
You know, I believe
miniature golf courses

24:32.572 --> 24:33.838
are designed by sadists.

24:33.840 --> 24:37.708
Were you at Tyler Bolander's
mini-golf birthday party?

24:37.710 --> 24:38.943
Oh, yeah,
yeah, yeah, yeah.

24:38.945 --> 24:43.080
Yeah, three kids ended up
in the emergency room.

24:43.082 --> 24:44.081
No, no, three?

24:44.083 --> 24:45.349
Try six.
What?

24:45.351 --> 24:46.016
Oh, that's right.

24:46.018 --> 24:48.719
Your mom came and picked you up
in a squad car.

24:48.721 --> 24:51.455
The fight got much worse
after you left.

24:51.457 --> 24:52.156
Ugh.

24:52.158 --> 24:54.024
We go back
a long way.

24:54.026 --> 24:56.494
Yeah, we do.
Kindergarten.

24:56.496 --> 24:57.428
Marcy Katz' class.

24:57.430 --> 24:59.230
Do you remember she told us
she was a lesbian?

24:59.232 --> 25:02.766
She came out to
a room of five-year-olds.

25:02.768 --> 25:04.668
You probably forgot
my class photo.

25:04.670 --> 25:05.870
Are you kidding me?

25:05.872 --> 25:06.570
Your bangs were--

25:06.572 --> 25:08.639
I don't need to see it
or relive it, thanks.

25:08.641 --> 25:11.542
And they lined up our photos,
and it was like boy,

25:11.544 --> 25:15.045
girl, girl, boy, monster.
Monster.

25:15.047 --> 25:17.548
Yes, always.

25:22.420 --> 25:24.889
You know what I realized?

25:26.224 --> 25:28.359
What?

25:28.361 --> 25:30.995
I am like your sister.

25:30.997 --> 25:35.065
Yeah, I guess so, huh?

25:40.238 --> 25:44.642
I'd be happy if you were
the only person in my life.

25:47.078 --> 25:50.281
Traveling from adventure
to adventure.

25:50.283 --> 25:51.382
Yeah, I'd like that.

25:51.384 --> 25:53.751
I've always wanted
to visit all 50 states.

25:53.753 --> 25:54.985
I really wanna go
to that place,

25:54.987 --> 25:57.721
you know, where you can stand
on all the four states

25:57.723 --> 25:58.489
at the same time?

25:58.491 --> 26:00.925
I wanna actually
live in Alaska.

26:00.927 --> 26:01.625
Really?

26:01.627 --> 26:02.693
Not forever,
but, like,

26:02.695 --> 26:04.328
just to say
that I've lived in Alaska.

26:04.330 --> 26:08.499
I wanna go to Utah and sell
hot tubs to rich skiers.

26:08.501 --> 26:10.801
That's your lifelong dream?

26:10.803 --> 26:13.437
No, I just made it up.

26:13.439 --> 26:15.005
Is that not--

26:15.007 --> 26:16.874
No?

26:20.178 --> 26:21.979
Carter, let's go.

26:21.981 --> 26:25.015
Let's do it.
We can do this.

26:25.017 --> 26:26.417
Crash.
No, I mean it.

26:26.419 --> 26:28.385
All right, I don't
wanna wait three years

26:28.387 --> 26:29.687
to start my life
with you.

26:29.689 --> 26:30.454
It's already started.

26:30.456 --> 26:31.922
And it's not gonna end
if you have to go

26:31.924 --> 26:33.023
to prison for a while.

26:33.025 --> 26:36.360
No, you think it won't,
but it will.

26:36.362 --> 26:38.195
Okay.

26:38.197 --> 26:41.165
Well, then,
have faith in me.

26:41.866 --> 26:43.934
I have faith in you.

26:46.404 --> 26:48.305
What?

26:48.307 --> 26:50.708
Crash, what's wrong?

26:50.710 --> 26:51.809
Sit down.

26:51.811 --> 26:54.144
Crash.

26:54.146 --> 26:57.414
Look, I don't want
three years

26:57.416 --> 27:01.218
of-- of you seeing me
in a-- a green jumpsuit

27:01.220 --> 27:04.755
in some dirty room being told
that you can't touch me, okay?

27:04.757 --> 27:07.291
I'd rather
you see me like this,

27:07.293 --> 27:08.859
even if it's for
the last time.

27:08.861 --> 27:10.361
Crash.

27:25.443 --> 27:27.945
Bye, Carter.

27:27.947 --> 27:30.981
Crash,
where are you going?

27:30.983 --> 27:33.384
Please don't go.

27:33.386 --> 27:35.753
Crash!

27:47.732 --> 27:51.468
<i>(cell phone rings)</i>

27:54.305 --> 27:55.739
Hello?

27:55.741 --> 27:57.574
(sighs)

27:57.576 --> 28:00.577
(sighs)
No.

28:00.579 --> 28:02.846
Have you heard from him?

28:02.848 --> 28:03.614
All right.

28:03.616 --> 28:06.216
Will you tell me
if you do?

28:06.218 --> 28:07.518
Thanks.

28:07.520 --> 28:08.819
Bye.

28:18.463 --> 28:19.930
When are they
going to invent a phone

28:19.932 --> 28:21.432
that rings
when you want it to?

28:21.434 --> 28:22.966
If it was
up to me, today.

28:22.968 --> 28:25.069
Wait, who are you
waiting to hear from?

28:25.071 --> 28:26.637
Max.

28:26.639 --> 28:28.305
Just call him.

28:28.307 --> 28:29.840
No.
Why?

28:29.842 --> 28:31.241
I wanna know
if he likes me,

28:31.243 --> 28:34.745
and I'll only know
if he calls me.

28:34.747 --> 28:37.681
Or, you know,
you could just ask him.

28:37.683 --> 28:41.085
Yeah, 'cause I'm such
an emotional daredevil.

28:41.087 --> 28:43.020
That's what I did
with Crash.

28:43.022 --> 28:44.354
That's you.

28:44.356 --> 28:45.389
It's not me.

28:45.391 --> 28:47.624
Taylor, are you really willing
to risk losing someone

28:47.626 --> 28:49.827
who you really like
just because you're too scared

28:49.829 --> 28:51.028
to ask them
if they like you?

28:51.030 --> 28:52.796
Come on,
you like Max, right?

28:52.798 --> 28:54.565
Yeah, a lot.

28:54.567 --> 28:57.167
Okay, well,
why take the risk?

28:57.169 --> 28:59.903
Look, you know what,
if there's anything I've learned

28:59.905 --> 29:00.704
in the last few months,

29:00.706 --> 29:03.674
it's that you never
actually know how much time

29:03.676 --> 29:05.075
you've got left
with someone.

29:05.077 --> 29:06.076
You know there's
all this stuff

29:06.078 --> 29:08.779
that I wish
I had said to my mom.

29:08.781 --> 29:09.880
And now there's
all this stuff

29:09.882 --> 29:11.582
I'm never gonna get
to say to Crash.

29:11.584 --> 29:14.318
What won't you
get to say to Crash?

29:14.320 --> 29:14.885
Everything.

29:14.887 --> 29:18.055
I don't even know what
I'm not gonna get to say to him.

29:18.057 --> 29:19.556
That's...

29:19.558 --> 29:21.792
that's the whole point.

29:23.228 --> 29:24.128
I'm sorry.

29:24.130 --> 29:25.429
This is my stuff.

29:25.431 --> 29:27.731
Max is not
gonna disappear on you.

29:27.733 --> 29:29.299
Is that what Crash
is doing?

29:29.301 --> 29:30.901
Well, I hope not,
but that's what

29:30.903 --> 29:32.035
it's starting to look like.

29:32.037 --> 29:33.070
You have to go get him.

29:33.072 --> 29:36.807
How? I have absolutely
no idea where he is.

29:36.809 --> 29:38.008
You have to.

29:38.010 --> 29:40.010
You're my role model.

29:42.914 --> 29:44.148
Fine.

29:44.682 --> 29:46.283
So, you'll see Max?

29:46.285 --> 29:48.719
You'll tell him
you like him?

29:48.721 --> 29:50.020
Yes.

29:50.022 --> 29:51.755
Come here.

29:51.757 --> 29:53.857
It's gonna be great,
I promise.

29:53.859 --> 29:55.425
Don't worry.

29:55.427 --> 29:57.027
Thanks.

30:03.701 --> 30:07.437
(sighs)
Hi, it's me.

30:08.840 --> 30:09.740
Look, Crash,

30:09.742 --> 30:12.409
this is the last message
I'm gonna leave you.

30:12.411 --> 30:13.844
You're gonna spend
your whole life

30:13.846 --> 30:16.113
running away
from your problems...

30:16.115 --> 30:17.514
running away from
the person

30:17.516 --> 30:20.384
that you're terrified
of becoming.

30:20.386 --> 30:23.020
But that's not life.

30:23.022 --> 30:24.488
Okay?
That's--

30:24.490 --> 30:25.722
That's just running
from it.

30:25.724 --> 30:28.592
And I know I've never
been in your position,

30:28.594 --> 30:29.259
or even close,

30:29.261 --> 30:31.495
but, Crash, I have spent
the last few months

30:31.497 --> 30:33.530
running away from stuff,
and I can tell you

30:33.532 --> 30:35.799
it is exhausting.

30:35.801 --> 30:37.768
Please don't let
the decisions you make now

30:37.770 --> 30:42.105
ruin the rest
of your life.

30:42.107 --> 30:45.876
Please come home.

30:45.878 --> 30:47.778
Please.

30:51.983 --> 30:54.651
<i>(phone beeps)</i>

30:58.890 --> 31:00.591
<i>(elevator dings)</i>

31:00.593 --> 31:03.293
Bird!

31:03.295 --> 31:04.061
Anything?

31:04.063 --> 31:07.564
I'm sorry,
nobody's seen him.

31:07.566 --> 31:08.498
(sighs)

31:08.500 --> 31:10.634
Carter, I think
you need to accept

31:10.636 --> 31:12.569
that he's not
gonna show up.

31:12.571 --> 31:14.504
I really think
that he might this time.

31:14.506 --> 31:16.607
That would mean
taking responsibility

31:16.609 --> 31:18.308
and recognizing
that he's made mistakes.

31:18.310 --> 31:20.010
And those are two things
Crash has never done.

31:20.012 --> 31:22.246
No, but I can't
just accept that.

31:22.248 --> 31:23.847
Carter, I know
he cares about you,

31:23.849 --> 31:25.515
but he's not gonna
go to jail just to prove

31:25.517 --> 31:28.986
that he's a good guy.

31:28.988 --> 31:30.888
It's time.

31:30.890 --> 31:33.523
Is he here?

31:33.525 --> 31:34.691
No, he's not.

31:34.693 --> 31:37.628
<i>(metal detector beeping)</i>

31:41.566 --> 31:43.567
Yes, he is.

31:43.569 --> 31:45.269
Hey!

31:46.571 --> 31:47.871
You came.

31:47.873 --> 31:50.107
Yeah, I did.

31:50.109 --> 31:52.175
Did you doubt me?

31:52.177 --> 31:53.343
No.

31:53.345 --> 31:55.779
That's why I'm here.

31:55.781 --> 31:57.648
Hey.
(Bird laughing)

31:57.650 --> 31:58.248
Hey.

31:58.250 --> 32:01.551
I'm stunned.
Yeah, me, too.

32:03.388 --> 32:05.722
Detective Wilson,

32:05.724 --> 32:07.124
should we go in?

32:07.126 --> 32:07.591
No.

32:07.593 --> 32:09.459
Could you please
stand over there?

32:09.461 --> 32:11.361
Why?

32:11.363 --> 32:14.264
Let's just
let them talk, okay?

32:17.969 --> 32:20.137
I talked to
your court-appointed counsel

32:20.139 --> 32:20.938
and the district attorney,

32:20.940 --> 32:22.973
and they agreed
to three years probation

32:22.975 --> 32:25.275
and 100 hours
community service.

32:25.277 --> 32:26.743
What?
It's done.

32:26.745 --> 32:28.178
Your court case is done.

32:28.180 --> 32:29.846
Can I hug you?
No!

32:29.848 --> 32:33.550
What?
What happened?

32:33.552 --> 32:35.018
I'm not going to prison.

32:35.020 --> 32:36.687
What?

32:36.689 --> 32:37.988
Oh, my God.

32:37.990 --> 32:40.057
Wait, he's-- he's not?

32:40.059 --> 32:41.325
Not today.

32:41.327 --> 32:42.059
Congratulations!

32:42.061 --> 32:43.760
Uh, Detective Wilson,
thank you.

32:43.762 --> 32:44.928
I-- I know
you did this. I--

32:44.930 --> 32:46.396
Carter, there's some
more things that I need

32:46.398 --> 32:48.231
to discuss
with Crash, okay?

32:48.233 --> 32:49.833
Please?

32:49.835 --> 32:51.768
It's cool.

32:51.770 --> 32:53.370
(girls tittering)

32:53.372 --> 32:56.206
You have
zero chances left.

32:56.208 --> 32:56.740
Zero.

32:56.742 --> 32:58.775
So, if you even so much
as light up a joint,

32:58.777 --> 33:00.844
you're gonna be behind bars
for three years,

33:00.846 --> 33:02.879
and then after that,
the next step

33:02.881 --> 33:05.749
is spending the rest
of your life in a cage.

33:05.751 --> 33:07.484
I want you to know
that I get it, all right?

33:07.486 --> 33:08.819
You did this because
you love your daughter

33:08.821 --> 33:12.055
more than you hate me,
but you won't be sorry.

33:12.057 --> 33:14.157
I'm going to do everything
in my power to--

33:14.159 --> 33:18.362
to prove to you that
I'm worthy of your daughter.

33:18.364 --> 33:21.999
So, thank you
for this chance

33:22.001 --> 33:24.301
to show you that...

33:24.303 --> 33:26.970
you're wrong about me.

33:50.995 --> 33:53.196
<i>(police radio chatter)</i>

33:53.198 --> 33:54.998
Oh, hey.
Hey.

33:55.000 --> 33:56.566
So, what did you think?

33:56.568 --> 33:57.501
Pretty nice, huh?

33:57.503 --> 33:59.202
The Park Grand?
What?

33:59.204 --> 34:00.370
You haven't been
to your desk?

34:00.372 --> 34:02.672
No, it's been
a very long day.

34:02.674 --> 34:03.206
I just got back.

34:03.208 --> 34:07.411
Mm, well, there's an envelope
on your desk with a key.

34:07.413 --> 34:08.211
Thanks.

34:08.213 --> 34:08.945
When can you leave?

34:08.947 --> 34:11.181
I'll just drop this off
then I'll grab my bag.

34:11.183 --> 34:12.416
(whispering)
Okay.

34:12.418 --> 34:13.650
Happy anniversary.

34:13.652 --> 34:16.086
(whispering)
Happy anniversary.

34:18.322 --> 34:20.223
(sighs)

34:20.225 --> 34:23.827
Hey, this should go
to the D.A.'s office.

34:23.829 --> 34:25.962
Thanks.

34:28.900 --> 34:29.633
(sighs)
Hi.

34:29.635 --> 34:32.135
Sorry, I didn't mean
to frighten you.

34:32.137 --> 34:34.337
Uh, that's okay.

34:34.339 --> 34:35.272
What's up?

34:35.274 --> 34:37.174
Uh, you forgot
your bathing suit.

34:37.176 --> 34:39.376
You're gonna need that,
aren't you?

34:39.378 --> 34:41.478
Yeah, definitely.
Thank you.

34:41.480 --> 34:42.112
That was stupid.

34:42.114 --> 34:43.980
So, your mom's
picking you up here?

34:43.982 --> 34:46.149
I'll hang out
till she comes.

34:46.151 --> 34:46.950
Great.

34:46.952 --> 34:50.253
I'll just grab my bag.
Oh, here, I got it.

34:50.255 --> 34:52.089
Do you want this?
Uh, leave it.

34:52.091 --> 34:53.890
I'll deal with it
tomorrow.

34:53.892 --> 34:57.561
<i>(cell phone buzzing)</i>
Oh...

34:57.563 --> 34:58.095
It's my mom.

34:58.097 --> 34:59.429
I've gotta take it.
Yeah, go ahead.

34:59.431 --> 35:01.098
I hope she doesn't
have to cancel.

35:01.100 --> 35:02.966
Right.

35:27.191 --> 35:31.461
<i>â™ª So put your hands up</i>
<i>if you feel it, hey â™ª</i>

35:31.463 --> 35:32.762
<i>(cell phone rings)</i>

35:32.764 --> 35:34.097
<i>â™ª .. if you</i>
<i>feel it, hey â™ª</i>

35:34.099 --> 35:38.201
<i>(ringing continues)</i>

35:38.203 --> 35:39.669
Oh, it's just Max.

35:39.671 --> 35:41.605
<i>(phone beeps)</i>

35:49.514 --> 35:50.380
Hi.

35:50.382 --> 35:52.182
Hey, uh--
(clears throat)

35:52.184 --> 35:55.519
This a bad time?
Yeah, kind of.

35:55.521 --> 35:57.754
Um, okay.

35:57.756 --> 35:58.188
I can go?

35:58.190 --> 36:00.023
Yeah, that's prob--
that's probably a good idea.

36:00.025 --> 36:01.992
I don't even
get a Skaddens?

36:01.994 --> 36:03.994
You don't get a what?

36:05.663 --> 36:06.229
Nothing.

36:06.231 --> 36:11.034
Um, it was just
this stupid callback.

36:11.036 --> 36:12.269
Bye.

36:12.271 --> 36:14.237
Bye.

36:15.473 --> 36:17.874
(sighs)

36:18.910 --> 36:22.279
<i>(door sensor chimes)</i>

36:22.281 --> 36:24.080
All right, she left.

36:24.082 --> 36:26.183
I really think
you should, too.

36:26.185 --> 36:28.285
Don't worry, Max.

36:28.287 --> 36:31.922
After tonight,
you'll never see me again.

36:35.326 --> 36:36.226
<i>â™ª (car radio plays)</i>

36:36.228 --> 36:40.397
<i>â™ª To say the things</i>
<i>I want to say â™ª</i>

36:40.399 --> 36:43.166
Hey, what did Max want?

36:43.168 --> 36:45.769
Oh, yeah, Max.

36:53.177 --> 36:53.843
What's wrong?

36:53.845 --> 36:56.379
Look at these--
like a hundred texts.

36:56.381 --> 36:59.015
Hang on,
I'm gonna call him.

37:01.419 --> 37:02.786
It's just going
to voicemail.

37:02.788 --> 37:04.321
We have to--
we have to go.

37:04.323 --> 37:05.755
Okay.

37:11.462 --> 37:13.363
<i>(door sensor chimes)</i>

37:13.931 --> 37:14.864
Max, what's wrong?

37:14.866 --> 37:16.333
You had me scared
out of my mind.

37:16.335 --> 37:19.002
And I guess I don't need
to ask what took so long.

37:19.004 --> 37:20.437
(Lori)
Carter?

37:23.207 --> 37:25.642
Oh, my God.

37:31.115 --> 37:34.251
(sighs)
Oh!

37:34.253 --> 37:37.687
(both laughing)

37:37.689 --> 37:39.289
Oh!

37:40.925 --> 37:42.459
Um...

37:44.061 --> 37:45.862
This is my mom.

37:45.864 --> 37:47.364
Yeah, I got that.

37:47.366 --> 37:49.833
This is Crash.
Hi.

37:49.835 --> 37:52.369
Great name.
Thanks.

37:52.371 --> 37:53.937
You realize
you're in the middle

37:53.939 --> 37:55.572
of a very well-lit store.

37:55.574 --> 37:57.040
Can we maybe...

37:57.042 --> 37:58.708
Come on.

38:03.681 --> 38:08.118
Oh!
(laughing)

38:08.120 --> 38:11.221
Mom, I can't--
when--

38:11.223 --> 38:14.124
How-- I can't even
string a sentence together.

38:14.126 --> 38:15.825
Are you okay?
Yes.

38:15.827 --> 38:17.294
Are you?
I'm perfect.

38:17.296 --> 38:19.896
We are going
to be together.

38:19.898 --> 38:20.497
How?

38:20.499 --> 38:21.231
I've got it all set up.

38:21.233 --> 38:22.699
It's gonna be a crazy,
fun adventure.

38:22.701 --> 38:26.636
Starting with
we have Russian passports.

38:27.405 --> 38:27.771
We do?

38:27.773 --> 38:29.005
I've-- I've taken care
of everything.

38:29.007 --> 38:32.842
All you need to do is go home
and pack a few things.

38:32.844 --> 38:34.110
You have a car?

38:34.112 --> 38:35.979
Uh, half a car.

38:35.981 --> 38:37.881
Okay, we're gonna need
the whole thing.

38:37.883 --> 38:42.085
Um, meet me here
tomorrow night.

38:42.087 --> 38:42.519
Tomorrow?

38:42.521 --> 38:45.088
I can't spend
another day apart from you.

38:45.090 --> 38:46.456
Isn't that how you feel?

38:46.458 --> 38:47.257
Yeah.

38:47.259 --> 38:49.392
Oh, um, here.

38:49.394 --> 38:50.894
You know what this is?

38:50.896 --> 38:52.696
Yeah, a burner phone.

38:52.698 --> 38:53.997
It's the story
of my life, though.

38:53.999 --> 38:55.131
In case you hit a snag.

38:55.133 --> 38:57.867
But it's only good
for one call.

38:58.936 --> 39:01.271
My shift's almost up.

39:01.273 --> 39:02.839
I'm not sure the next guy's
gonna be up

39:02.841 --> 39:04.874
for hosting
"America's Most Wanted."

39:04.876 --> 39:07.310
You used to be so cool.

39:08.579 --> 39:10.747
So did you.

39:10.749 --> 39:13.149
(scoffs)
Come here.

39:13.151 --> 39:18.088
Oh... I am so happy
right now.

39:18.090 --> 39:19.289
Love you.

39:19.291 --> 39:19.956
I love you, too.

39:19.958 --> 39:22.792
I think I already forgot
how it goes.

39:22.794 --> 39:24.694
Oh, sorry.

39:24.696 --> 39:28.998
I just-- it's been so long
since we said...

39:29.000 --> 39:30.834
um, love you.

39:30.836 --> 39:32.802
Love you more.
Not possible.

39:32.804 --> 39:35.105
Yes possible.

39:45.149 --> 39:49.018
I'm gonna miss
calling you "Carter."

39:54.358 --> 39:57.660
